  </li>
  <li>Visit Rules section, select Page Rules and click Create Page Rule
  <br>
    <img class="imgDir no-mobile" src="https://cdn.glitch.global/65f2254a-8e40-4b88-aae8-bb42a288bd4d/Screenshot%202023-03-23%20at%2010.12.54%20PM.png?v=1679625178855">  <img class="imgDir" src="https://cdn.glitch.global/65f2254a-8e40-4b88-aae8-bb42a288bd4d/Screenshot%202023-03-23%20at%2010.30.08%20PM.png?v=1679625194131">
    <ul class="no-mobile">
      <li>
        This may not work properly if you have colliding Page Rules. Re-route or remove redirects if you notice any issues.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>
   Test your custom domain works by visiting <code>/example</code>!<br>You'll still need to visit 0tr.me to shorten URLs, but now you can share short links with your own domain.

  </li>
</ol>
